                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>The stone is inscribed with a Roman-letter inscription (2) in four lines. The lines are understood to read vertically downwards but with the two top lines read together before the bottom two lines. There is an Ogham inscription (1) assumed to start at the stones bottom-left edge, reading vertically upwards. There is no record to suggest execution type of the inscriptions (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 233-5).</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>The Roman-letter inscription is <q>transcribed as light Roman capitals with ligaturing...it appears that there is an opening two-stroke C in two flat curves, NT join, AT conjoint in PATER, MA ligatured (as in Llywel (Pentre Poeth) 1 (B42), the 'Trecastle Stone'). Complete ligature of IUNT. Irregular layout, no apparent writing line</q> (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 235). The letters in the Ogham inscription are widely spaced. The execution of the inscriptions cannot be further discerned as the inscriptions survive only in a drawing (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 233-5).
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
